"""
aq-health-spider — Real service health sampling + autonomous fix pipeline.

Per cycle (default 900s / 15m — configurable via --interval):
  1. HTTP health check each zone (5s timeout, non-blocking)
  1b. Dashboard semantic probes for high-value operator cards
  2. Systemd service active-state check (on HTTP failure only, to save bandwidth)
  3. AppArmor denial scan since last cycle (kernel journal, deduped)
  4. Anomaly classification → fix pipeline dispatch

Fix pipeline (no sudo — user gates nixos-rebuild):
  apparmor_denial  → apparmor-fix-agent.py → commit rules → notify via HANDOFF.md
  service_down     → PRSI cycle (low-risk restart request)
  http_failure     → emit event + seed RAG error-solutions

Knowledge loop:
  Novel issues seeded to Qdrant error-solutions via llama-embed + Qdrant PUT.
  Structured events appended to .agents/telemetry/hybrid-events.jsonl.
  Fix summaries appended to .agent/collaboration/HANDOFF.md.
"""

